    DiaMetrics

    DiaMetrics is a web-based educational resource for exploring important concepts regarding binary classification (and its evaluation), which is important in many different fields such as psychodiagnostics (e.g. in determining cut-off values for tests), machine learning or medical testing.

    MindField

    "Mind Field" is a documentary-style series by Michael Stevens (Vsauce) that explores psychology, neuroscience, and human behavior through experiments and real-world scenarios. Covering topics like isolation, consciousness, and AI, the show delves into how the brain works and how external factors shape our thoughts and actions.

About

I started keeping this list because my bookmarks in the browser have simply become too cluttered and I have often received comments like ‘How do you always find such cool videos/websites?’. Honestly, I can't really answer this question, but for everyone else: Here you go, a list of all my favourite free, interesting and entertaining websites.

Please note the information below:

  • This is a private hobby project. I do not claim to list *every* great resource here.
  • I cannot guarantee that all links will work forever, I cannot vouch for the safety, usefulness, timeliness, etc. of the linked resources.
  • There is no advertising here, and no content is sponsored. All content has been selected because I personally like it, find it useful or entertaining. The content is therefore naturally based on my personal interests. But maybe there's something here that you'll like.
  • That is why you will also find content that I have created myself. These are transparently flagged as “shameless-self-plug”.
